From: PureCloak Authors <purecloak-dev@purecloak.org>
Date: Sat, 20 Jun 2026 20:30:00 +0800
Subject: SOCKS5 UDP ASSOCIATE support for QUIC proxying (#51)

Add Socks5UdpClientSocket that tunnels QUIC (and other UDP) traffic
through a SOCKS5 UDP ASSOCIATE relay. The socket performs a SOCKS5
handshake over TCP, then sends/receives RFC 1928 UDP encapsulated
packets through the relay UDP port.

Three components:
1. New Socks5UdpClientSocket class implementing DatagramClientSocket,
   with a state-machine-based SOCKS5 handshake, lazy init support for
   the synchronous Connect() path, and automatic SOCKS5 UDP header
   stripping on Read().
2. Wire QuicSessionPool::CreateSocket() to detect the
   --proxy-server=socks5://host:port command-line flag and create
   Socks5UdpClientSocket instead of the default UDPClientSocket.
3. Include guards and buildflag checks to ensure PureCloak-only code.

This enables QUIC (HTTP/3) traffic to be proxied through a SOCKS5
relay, preventing UDP-based QUIC connections from bypassing the proxy
and leaking the real IP address.

